  <bioghist encodinganalog="545"> 
    <head>Biography of Branson Graves Stevenson</head><p>B.G. Stevenson and his brothers, Lon C., Grover, J.H., and John T., created the Sunburst Oil &amp; Gas Company to develop a discovery well in the Kevin-Sunburst oil field in Montana in the 1920s. B.G. Stevenson was sales manager of the company, which was successful in producing oil. Stevenson remained in the oil industry, later working for Socony Mobil Oil Company, while also pursuing a career as an artist and potter.</p>
	 
  </bioghist> 
  <scopecontent encodinganalog="520"> 
    <head>Scope and Content</head><p>The B.G. Stevenson collection contains photographs, newspaper clippings, and correspondence regarding the Sunburst Oil &amp; Gas Company and its successor the Sunburst Oil &amp; Refining Company; the Kevin Sunburst oil field; road oiling operations in Great Falls, Montana; and other information on oil development in Montana.</p>
	 
  </scopecontent> 
